<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Montia</i> <i>fontana</i> and/or <i>Sidalcea</i> <i>calycosa</i> is co-dominant or characteristically present in the herbaceous layer with <i>Blennosperma</i> <i>nanum</i>, <i>Callitriche</i> <i>marginata</i>, <i>Castilleja</i> <i>campestris</i> ssp. <i>succulenta</i>, <i>Centromadia</i> <i>fitchii</i>, <i>Cicendia</i> <i>quadrangularis</i>, <i>Crassula</i> <i>aquatica</i>, <i>Downingia</i> <i>cuspidata</i>, <i>Gratiola</i> <i>heterosepala</i>, <i>Lasthenia</i> <i>fremontii</i>, <i>Limnanthes</i> <i>douglasii</i> ssp. <i>rosea</i>, <i>Mimulus</i> <i>guttatus</i>, <i>Plagiobothrys</i> <i>glyptocarpus</i>, <i>Plagiobothrys</i> <i>stipitatus</i>, <i>Trifolium</i> <i>depauperatum</i> and <i>Trifolium</i> <i>variegatum</i>. Other common species include <i>Hordeum</i> <i>marinum</i>, <i>Hypochaeris</i> <i>glabra</i> or <i>Lolium</i> <i>perenne</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 90 cm; cover is intermittent to continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Montia fontana</i> and/or <i>Sidalcea calycosa</i> are present as characteristic species in the herbaceous layer along with other diagnostic vernal pool species such as <i>Lasthenia fremontii</i>(Barbour et al. 2007).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Volcanic rock pools atop island-like mesas. Soils are shallow and rocky with short inundation periods. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Montia fontana</i> and subspecies as FACW/OBL plants and <i>Sidalcea calycosa</i> as an OBL plant. </div>
</div>

        
