    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Great Valley</b> (262Ab). Stands of the <i>Montia fontana-Sidalcea calycosa</i> association occur in the northeastern Sacramento Valley (Keeler-Wolf 1998a) on pool edges with those of the <i>Lasthenia glaberrima- Pogogyne douglasii</i> association in pool bottoms (Barbour et al. 2007b).</li>
        
            <li><b>Sierra Nevada Foothills</b> (M261Fa-c). Stands of the <i>Montia fontana-Sidalcea calycosa</i> association occur in the northern to southern subsections.</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> Threats are primarily from loss of habitat due to conversion to agriculture and development. However, threats also include invasive non-natives, such as <i>Hordeum marinum </i>and <i>Lolium perenne, </i>commonly found in this alliance. </div>
</div>

    

    

